.TH "nilfs_ioctl_wrap_copy" 9 "nilfs_ioctl_wrap_copy" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nilfs_ioctl_wrap_copy \- wrapping function of get/set metadata info
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" nilfs_ioctl_wrap_copy
.BI "(struct the_nilfs *nilfs "  ","
.BI "struct nilfs_argv *argv "  ","
.BI "int dir "  ","
.BI "ssize_t (*dofunc)(struct the_nilfs *, __u64 *, int, void *, size_t, size_t) "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "nilfs" 12
nilfs object
.IP "argv" 12
vector of arguments from userspace
.IP "dir" 12
set of direction flags
.IP "dofunc" 12
concrete function of get/set metadata info
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fBnilfs_ioctl_wrap_copy\fP gets/sets metadata info by means of
calling \fBdofunc\fP function on the basis of \fIargv\fP argument.

Return Value: On success, 0 is returned and requested metadata info
is copied into userspace. On error, one of the following
negative error codes is returned.

-EINVAL - Invalid arguments from userspace.

-ENOMEM - Insufficient amount of memory available.

-EFAULT - Failure during execution of requested operation.
